==English==
===Alternative spellings===
:[[tesselate]] (chiefly U.S.)

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-tessellate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Intransitive verb===
'''to tessellate''' (tessellating, tessellated)

#(''geometry'') Of a [[two-dimensional]] shape, such that multiple copies of itself placed edge to edge cover an area leaving no space between the shapes.
#:''[[Regular]] [[hexagon]]s tessellate.''

===Transitive verb===
'''to tessellate''' (tessellating, tessellated)

#(''geometry'') Of one or more two-dimensional shapes, to completely fill (an area) when multiple copies are placed edge to edge.
#:''It is possible to tessellate the [[plane]] with [[equilateral triangle]]s and [[regular]] hexagons.''

